  "prompt": "Can tax exemption be availed on tax saving FD for the entire tenure of 5 years by investing 1.5 lakhs in the 1st year?",
  "response": "In India, tax-saving fixed deposits (FDs) that fall under Section 80C of the Income Tax Act allow you to claim a deduction of up to \u20b91.5 lakhs in a financial year. However, the important aspect to note is that the \u20b91.5 lakh limit is for the total contributions made during the financial year. \n\nIf you invest \u20b91.5 lakhs in a tax-saving FD in the first year, you can claim the entire amount as a deduction under Section 80C for that financial year. However, tax-saving FDs typically have a lock-in period of 5 years, meaning the principal amount will remain invested for that duration, but you can only claim the deduction for the year when the investment is made. \n\nOnce you make the investment, you cannot claim further deductions for the same deposit in subsequent years, even if the FD is still active. So, while the FD will mature after 5 years, you\u2019ll get the tax benefit only for the year you invested, which is the first year in this case.\n\nIn summary:\n\n- You can claim a deduction of \u20b91.5 lakhs in the first year.\n- You cannot claim additional deductions in subsequent years for that same FD investment. \n\nAlways consult a tax advisor or financial expert for advice tailored to your specific circumstances.",
